The paper focuses on person re-identification, which is a computer vision task, and proposes a novel generative adversarial network to address cross-resolution person re-ID. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also advances adversarial learning techniques, which falls under cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper mentions experiments on vehicle re-ID benchmarks, which could fall under cs.MM (Multimedia). The proposed model also learns resolution-invariant image representations, which could fall under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper discusses the use of the proposed approach in real-world scenarios, which could fall under cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
